\begin_layout Plain Layout
First and foremost, I would like to express my deepest gratitude to my thesis
 advisors, Prof.
 Marc C Jacob, Dr.
 Vincent Clair, and Prof.
 Michel Roger, for their unwavering support, insightful guidance, and invaluable
 feedback throughout this research journey.
 Their expertise, patience, and encouragement were instrumental in shaping
 this work and helping me navigate challenges along the way.
 Prof.
 Marc's supervision is the major pillar of this work.
 Dr.
 Vincent Clair's reasonable interactions and suggestions regarding the research
 from has enabled a comfortable progress from early on.
 Special thanks to Prof.Michel Roger for many of his ideas and suggestions.
 Apart from formal supervision, my heart felt gratitude to Dr.
 Jerome Boudet whose sharing of knowledge and time to assist me in the process
 of this thesis was instrumental to its completion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
My heartfelt thanks go to my colleagues and peers at Ecole Centrale de Lyon,
 for their camaraderie, stimulating discussions, and technical assistance.
 The collaborative environment fostered by this group made the research
 process both productive and enjoyable.
 I wish to mention the members of my Thesis Monitoring Committee, Dr.
 Thomas Castelain and Dr.
 Sebastien Besset, who were instrumental in guiding me through the difficult
 terrain of the completion of PhD life.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Special thanks to Prof.
 Sergey Karabasov and Prof.
 Rob Krams of Queen Mary University London, and his research team for their
 unwavering support both personally and professionally during this academic
 journey.
 From managing life as an international research student to invigorating
 the collaborative research spirit, their timely contributions were inevitable
 to complete this journey.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
I am eternally grateful to my family — my parents, and siblings — for their
 unconditional love, endless encouragement, and sacrifices that enabled
 me to pursue my academic goals.
 My mother's belief in me has been a constant source of motivation and continues
 to fuel my quest for higher successes.
 My heartfelt gratitude extends to my dearest family friend Dr.
 Koshy Idicula, Kerala, India, and his family, for being my strength and
 an invisible guardian to my family in my absence at home.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
To all my friends including Ananthu, Augustin, Isa, Marie and Igor, Nathan,
 Stephano and Livia, thank you for your moral supports, laughter, games,
 night outs, homely dinners, and also mindful understanding during difficult
 times.
 You reminded me to stay grounded and persevere even when the path seemed
 daunting.
 To those who chose not to be friends in this brief journey, thank you for
 motivating me to be careful with my unconditional camaraderie.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Finally, I acknowledge the financial and institutional support provided
 by Airbus, and the early support from its engineers, namely, Dr.
 Florian Guiho, Dr.
 Maxime Itasse, and Dr.
 Nicolas Molin, which made this research possible.
 The resources, facilities, and opportunities offered were critical to the
 completion of this project.
\end_layout

